Anonymous CVS is available for the "guile-sdl" module.
Here are the commands to use:

  cvs -d :pserver:anonymous@cvs.glug.org:/home/ttn/cvsroot login
	 # just type RET at the prompt

  cvs co guile-sdl

Look at autogen.sh to get started.

Here are some cvs tags and their meanings:

  ok-1   -- passes "make && make check"
  ok-2   -- like ok-1, plus doc snarfing (doc/guile-sdl.info available)
  ok-3   -- like ok-2, plus "make install" (w/ module catalog update)
  ok-4   -- like ok-3, using GH_ macros instead of MDEF*
  ok-5   -- like ok-4, without "sdl-" prefix (examples all use #:renamer)
  ok-6   -- like ok-5, using GUILE_LIBSITE_DIR configure.in macro


Happy hacking!
